content.text:
A try-catch block is written as follows:
try {
  // Code that might cause an error
}
catch (exception_type variable) {
  // Handle the exception
}
`exception_type` specifies the type of exception (e.g., `std::exception`, `int`, `std::string`), and `variable` holds the exception's content.

